data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
If no custom stylesheet (XSLT-file) is entered, the "Extract" operation will use the built-in XSLT stylesheet. This stylesheet will extract all structured tags (content controls) in the docx file, along with embedded text.
To develop a custom XSLT stylesheet, use the raw Open XML output as your starting point.

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
This tool makes it possible, without having Microsoft Word installed, to: * Quickly get a complete view of the Open XML content of any valid DOCX file * Extract tagged content as XML from the valid DOCX - either using the built-in stylesheet or by adding your own custom XSLT stylesheet * Save the results locally
The built-in stylesheet, which will be used if no custom XSLT is provided, will extract any text content marked up with standard Open XML content controls as well as information about tag-name/alias.
Of course, using a custom stylesheet, you can design different extraction strategies and formats, as needed.
To develop a custom XSLT, start with the raw, flat Open XML that you can generate with this tool as your XML input - and use the default XSLT (provided through GitHub) as the XSLT starting point.
